  "texts": [
    "One way to harmonize the different datasets which use either ontologies A or B would then to develop a new ontology X which captures information about curfews, lockdowns, restrictions of public gatherings over 100 people, restrictions of public gatherings over 200 people and travel bans.",
    "Another way to would be to develop a new ontology Y which captures information about (i) curfews, lockdowns, restrictions of public gatherings and travel bans and (ii) how many people are restricted from gathering publicly (e.g. 100 or 200).",
    "Both ontologies X and Y would be examples of developing a global ontology to harmonize ontologies A and B.",
    "Mapping meanwhile creates a set of rules to relate different taxonomies or ontologies to each other.",
    "A benefit of this approach is that original information in a given dataset can be preserved but a drawback is that mappings can become complicated if many-to-one mappings are necessary or one-to-one mappings are not possible."
  ],
